#!/usr/bin/env python3
# =============================================================================
# kwin_realign.py
# Generated by: Claude Sonnet 4.6
#
# Drift-correction utility for wayland-desktop.
#
# Corrects window placement without launching any applications.  All windows
# must already be running; this script only moves and re-tiles them.
#
# Motivation
# ----------
# KWin stores tile position per (window, desktop) pair.  When kwin_restore.py
# places a window on desktop 1 and then sets it to appear on all desktops,
# the tile is correct on desktop 1 but may differ on other desktops.  After
# an extended period of inactivity (e.g. screen-lock unlock) the window
# positions can drift further.  This script corrects that drift.
#
# Loop structure
# --------------
# Outer loop: every virtual desktop in order.
#   Inner loop: every entry in the YAML setup file.
#     Default mode (no --all-apps):
#       Process only entries with on_all_desktops=True.
#     --all-apps mode:
#       Process entries with on_all_desktops=True on every desktop.
#       Process entries with a specific desktop only when the outer loop
#       is on that matching desktop.
#
# For each (desktop, entry) pair:
#   1. switch_to_desktop(desktop)
#   2. Locate the live window (session_state → resourceClass scan fallback)
#   3. move_to_screen to anchor the window on the correct screen
#   4. Apply tile / maximize / minimize / raise
#
# After all desktops are processed, the originally active desktop is restored.
#
# Window lookup
# -------------
# Primary:  session_state.json  tracking_uuid → internalId
#           Written by kwin_restore.py after phase 1; stale entries from
#           previous boot sessions are pruned automatically.
# Fallback: live scan of workspace.windowList() by resourceClass
#           Used when session state is absent, empty, or missing this entry.
#
# USAGE:
#   python3 kwin_realign.py [OPTIONS] [APP]
#
# ARGUMENTS:
#   APP                 (optional) Realign only this app (alias or
#                       resourceClass).  Equivalent to --filter APP.
#
# OPTIONS:
#   --setup FILE        Snapshot/setup file to read from.
#                       If omitted, reads default_setup from config.yaml and
#                       searches in: current dir, ~/.config/wayland-desktop/,
#                       snapshot_dir.
#   --config FILE       Alternate config file
#   --all-apps          Process all entries, not just on_all_desktops ones.
#                       Single-desktop entries are processed only on their
#                       own desktop.
#   --dry-run           Show what would be done without changing anything
#   --settle-delay MS   Milliseconds to wait after each desktop switch
#                       (default: 400)
#   --verbose           Print a debug line after every KWin script call
#   --show-window       Show the progress window regardless of config
#   --no-window         Suppress the progress window regardless of config
#   --filter APP        Only realign this app alias or resourceClass
#                       (repeatable; combined with APP positional)
# =============================================================================
#
